  "body": "It would be useful to have an `isOptional` member to negate `isRequired`.\n\nuse case:\n\n```\nconst ThingList = ({things}) => (\n    <ul>\n        {things.map(thing => <li>{thing.name}</li>)}\n    </ul>\n);\n\nThingList.propTypes = {\n    things: PropTypes.arrayOf(PropTypes.shape({name:PropTypes.string.isRequired})).isRequired\n};\n\nconst Whatever = ({things, title}) => (\n    <div>\n        <h1>{title}</h1>\n\n        {things && things.length\n            ? <ThingList things={things} />\n            : null}\n    </div>\n);\n\nWhatever.propTypes = {\n    things: ThingList.propTypes.things.isOptional,\n    title: PropTypes.node\n};\n```\n\nThe `things` property is required for `ThingList`, but `Whatever` conditionally renders `things` if they were passed to it. `Whatever` reuses `ThingList`'s propType but makes it optional. This would alleviate the need to make a separate `thingShape` variable for everything before the `.isRequired` to be referenced by `ThingList` and `Whatever`.\n",
